Aug 14 2009 	Can't beat the location but needs a makeover	Our group finally decided to go on the group trip that we had been planning for well over a decade. The economic times put us on a budget, so when we found the Tropicana on Orbitz as part of a package deal we picked it up.As with most things you get what you pay for, but overall the Tropicana provided good value for the price. For a hotel on the Strip, you can't beat the location - close to the airport and with Excalibur, Luxor, Mandalay Bay, New York New York, and MGM Grand all either within easy walking distance or a tram ride away.Our rooms were in the Island Tower, which is the farthest from the entrance to the casino. The beds were comfortable, though the decor was a bit dated with a bit of peeling wallpaper. In short, nothing fancy - kinda like a Holiday Inn with craps tables. When we were there, there were a few infrastructure problems - an escalator under repair, plus a problem with the elevator call buttons (you could only call an up elevator and might go for a ride in order to go down).As for the staff, though, the bell staff were very helpful. As for the housekeeping service: generally OK, except for the one night we came back to the room briefly at about 8 p.m. only to find the room had not been cleaned. We called the front desk before we left and found it cleaned when we got back. On the casino floor, we ran into some of the nicest craps dealers on our last day there.For our purposes, though, we were satisfied with the hotel. Overall, the Tropicana is a good choice for someone who thinks of the hotel as a place to sleep, and not necessarily a place to spend the day.	
