Jul 17 2009 	Don't Worry... it was GREAT!	We were at the Tropicana from July 7 thru 10th. After reading the reviews on here we were very worried that it would be a total dump...but we were pleasantly surprised that it was actually a really nice hotel - and I'm a complete hotel snob!ALL of the staff we interacted with were incredibly friendly and helpful. Our room on the 18th floor of the Island Tower was CLEAN, ie: NO bedbugs and had a brand new and very comfy mattress! Yeah, the decore is a bit dated, gotta love the bamboo mirrors on the ceiling...but it wasn't as bad as people make it out to be on tripadvisor. Ok, so there was a bit of tape on occasional spots on the carpet in the main walkways, but at least we weren't tripping over frayed carpet! The hotel was built in the 1950's and has a great, cheezy Vegas charm to it. The bartenders were awesome, especially Jason and Lorenzo. We had a great time hanging out with them! The pool was awesome as well!!!I've stayed at the Monte Carlo and Luxor in Vegas before and the Tropicana topped both these hotels in service and comfort. We will DEFINETLY be staying here again!!!	
Jul 16 2009 	A classic in need of some updating and upkeep	In one of the hallways at the Tropicana, there are pictures of Vegas from the Late 50's and early 60's, and the Tropicana was there. You can even recognize some of the building today amid the towers and the newer pool. To me, that added to my stay at the Tropicana. This Classic hotel is in major need of an update. It seems like every hallway has a different set of doors or decor. This is Vegas of the past. This is not the Vegas of New York New York, or the Venician or Paris etc. etc. The Tropicana is part of the kitchy, glitzy, cheap neon fun Vegas, where you by 3 Tshirs for $10.00. My room was at the Island Tower. When I walked in, I chuckled and had a wide grin on my face. The Bed had a &quot;Ceiling Mirror&quot; As a 44 year old male, I felt transported to a time when I was 10 and I would overhear Adults talk about the &quot;bad&quot; Vegas, where people went to do Adult things. To top it off, it was decorated like disco was still king. I have to say that the room was clean and the staff I came in contact with was very friendly. If this was not the Tropicana, I would have told you to Run and Run fast. But it is a Classic, and take it for what it is.	
