Jul 11 2009 	You get what you pay for	This was our fourth stay at the Trop. It has an ideal location on the strip, minutes walk away from all of the big casinos and only a short (cheap) cab ride from the airport.The MGM monorail is just across the road, giving access all the way up to the Sahara.Rates are very good for what is essentially a place to put your head and have a shower. If you are after a spa resort, excellent room service, in hotel dining and a place where you don't have to leave the hotel, then don't stay at the Trop!If you are after a budget, centre strip hotel with good pool, then this is the place for you.We do not recommend the buffet - just walk across to Excalibur which has a fantastic breakfast or great &quot;eat all day&quot; deal.Dirk Arthur's Extreme Magic really has to be seen to be believed! If you win free tickets, or get given tickets with your room, then you get what you pay for!!!!! If you want to kill an hour in a run down theatre whilst some pretty average magic is performed, or you watch a video on preserving endangered big cats, then go for it!!In summary, don't go to the Trop with major expectations. Go for what it is. Excellent value, excellent location, and do everything else in other hotels on the strip!	
