Jun 12 2009 	Great older hotel. Friendly staff good food best pool in Las Vegas.	Our room was spacious and the tub was huge -- could almost swim in it. It was nice to have a refrigerator. The pool area was fantastic. Waterfalls (that you can walk under), hot tubs hidden away, and an island to swim to. The pool alone is worth the visit. The food in the steak house was exceptional and was reasonably priced. The 24 hour cafe had great views and good breakfasts. There is a massive stained glass ceiling over part of the casino that is definitely Old Las Vegas. I liked it so much, I'm using it as my &quot;name&quot;.My only concern is that the televisions in the rooms are small and ancient -- needs upgraded. Also, it does not have 24 hour room service.	
