 family also stayed in &quot;Island Towers&quot; but they were on levels 18 &amp; 19. They seemed to have newer mattresses (within 5 years) that were comfy. The rest of the room was the same as ours, dirty carpet, etc. I don't know if they decided to upgrade some floors, or are working on it, but I would stay in a room in the &quot;Paradise Towers&quot; to be safe if you HAVE to stay here.I am 23, a college student, and there is no way I'd reccommend this place to my friends. I travel a lot, and am aware that older hotels are going to have older mattresses and be a little outdated. This shouldn't be the case for a &quot;resort&quot; that is right in the center of the strip and entertainment.The wedding was beautiful, the pool was nice, and room service for food and extra pillows was very speedy and friendly. In my opinion though, I would take bad service to a peed on bed any day. I will not stay here again. BEWARE!	
