Feb 26 2009 	Great location for the bargain searcher	Two thirty year old married (not to each other) guys looking to have a fun weekend away. Good location on the south end of the strip. If you are watching the pennies, this is it! You can walk across the bridge to MGM and eat at a nice McDonald's. Sign up or the player's club and claim your free Trop T-Shirt, deck of cards and coupons or the tables. The Garden Rooms are the old one or two story buildings in the middle. We were offered one of these w/two beds OR an Island Tower Room with a King and a fold out couch. We chose the latter and had a view of the airport. Because there are way more Island Tower Rooms, i assuming most get this option to upgrade from garden for free. So I recommend to always book Garden and see if they upgrade you for free. Ate at the cafe and the prices were reasonable. Indoor pool and spa is nothing huge, but is year round. Went to Studio 54 at MGM Grand- wasn't really impressed. Go to Moon/Playboy at the Palms if you want to have an experience. And if you are going clubbing, go on eBay and get your passes that way for about $2 or $3 a piece. Search eBay for &quot;Las Vegas Passes.&quot; I do this everytime! I am in the process of putting a trip together in mid March 09 and will most likely book the Trop again. Oh- And I saw a buy one get one free poster on the Excalibur for their buffet from 2pm - 4pm. Arizona drivers: avoid the dam and go through Laughlin to be safe. We waited 2 full hours at the dam and it sucked! Enjoy your Vegas trip and bring your own drinks :-)	
