Feb 12 2009 	The old lady's gone downhill but you might consider it	In Diamonds Are Forever, Sean Connery mumbled as James Bond that he &quot;heard that the Tropicana is quite comfortable.&quot; Back in the day when what is now the MGM Grand was still their golf course, it was one of the premier properties on the Strip -- the upper floor jacuzzi suites were about as good as it got -- but they have more-or-less stood still for the past thirty years. The rooms in the Island Tower haven't been materially updated for that long.Though the Trop has evolved into more of a place for the budget traveler, it does have one spectacular amenity: the pool. On weekends, you can still play swim-up blackjack or get a free back massage under the waterfall (why pay $10 for the same thing at one of the massage machines?) at one of the nicest pools in town. Get yourself a yard-long fru-fru drink (Under the Waterfall is a classic), lather on the sun creme, slip a $100 chip into your bathing shorts for the black-jack, and take a nice nap. The bikini quotient has fallen dramatically, but you'll still enjoy it.Even if you don't stay there, if you do visit and want a good laugh, step into the front tower elevator and take a short ride. When you reach the casino floor, the elevator recording announces, in one of the most deliciously sarcastic tones this side of Don Rickles, &quot;Casino! Good luck!&quot;The rack rates in Vegas are obscene, and no one pays them unless there is a major fight in town. But if you are not a gambler, you want the Strip experience, and you don't want to break the bank to get it, the Trop may be one of the best values out there.	
Feb 6 2009 	Tropicanna resort Hotel not that bad	Having read some of the reviews of the hotel I was worried and very annoyed at my husband for booking it, even tho he said it was a bargain.Luckily it was nowhere near as bad as expected. We stayed in an island tower room which was very dated but clean and we could not fault the room cleaner even tho we never saw her as we spent most time out and about. You dont visit Vegas to sit in your room to complain. We had a room overlooking the airport but we had fabulous sunrises and sunsets over the mountains.We made a decision before we arrived not to eat in the same hotel twice. We ate the first night in the Tropicanna buffet and it was the worst meal of the holiday.The hotel staff where all very helpful especially one cocktail waitress who I cant remember her name or I would have given her a mention. We made two trips to the Grand Canyon one by plane to the South rim and then a helicopter tour and the other to the North rim by Bus. Both where fantastic and are a must.All in all we had a great time, the hotel does need updating but if you have booked the Tropicanna dont worry its not that bad.We will definitely go back to Vegas my husband said he would stay again at the Tropicanna (he loves a bargain) I would like to stay some where new. Not sure who will win.	
Feb 3 2009 	Best Deal in Vegas!	For the price it can't be beat. We had a very large room with all the amenities. The staff have really upped their game with smiles and courtesy.And other than Mandalay Bay, we won more at the Trop than any other casino we gambled in.It's very convienent to all the other great casinos, and I agree with the other travelers, that the constant badgering from the time share people does get old, but that's a small bother compared to the overall experience.If you want to impress people, or you need new and fancy, the Trop is not the way to go, but if you want a descent room, and a great location for little dough, go with the Trop.	
