Dec 17 2008 	Very outdated...worst part-BEDBUGS	My husband won two free nights at The Tropicana in a golf outing. We added another night for a long weekend getaway. We were looking for clean and comfortable. We knew this was not the fanciest place on the strip. We have stayed in many different places in Vegas from all price ranges (from Caesers Palace to Imperial Palace to Ellis Island). These rooms at The Tropicana have not been updated since the early 70s. The bathroom still has a metal kleenex box holder mounted on the edge on the bathroom counter. The towels are thin, small and dingy white. The soap and shampoo were the the worst Ive seen and the water was so hard, nothing lathered no matter what quality it was. The bathtub had a textured nonslip bottom that was gray and dirty. The toilet was chipped and stained. The oddest thing is the tiki style huge mirrors mounted on the ceiling over the bed, on the wall and on the headboard. It just screamed &quot;sleazy&quot;. The worst part of our stay occured after an afternoon nap. I awoke with a start and a feeling on my neck of a tiny bite. I instinctively reached up and &quot;caught&quot; someothing under my finger. It was a bedbug. Ive seen the news shows about bedbugs and I know what they look like. I also know that bedbugs are becoming a bigger problem in all places with the increase of international travel and they can be carried on luggage. All the rationalizing in the world did not make me feel any more sympathetic toward the hotel about my first experience with them. My husband asked if we should change rooms but there is no way of knowing if a room has them until you sleep there as the bugs rise out of the mattress in response to a persons body heat. I saw no other signs of bedbug infestation (ie small brownish spots on mattress or headboard).  We ended up finding several more the following morning but by then it was time to leave...thank goodness. I should have brought it to the attention of the staff but I didnt. I guess because there is not much they can do about it during our stay.  I decided to write this review to warn others. I read some other reviews that also experienced bedbugs here. We will not stay here again as I know there are other places in Vegas that are alot nicer and price comparable.	
