er and told her my situation and she wasnt willing to do anything about it, she even had the nerve to tell us &quot;well you should of selected the paradise tower room and this might have happend&quot;. i was like what the hell... i dont think so, i told her that had no reveleance to this, she explained she could issue us new keys, i asked her well is there anything else you could do for the inconvenice and she said NO!!, In an attitude. I then told her i would like to be transffered to another room and she said no because none were available. i got mad and started to raise my voice, she then spoke to her supervisor and thats when she said i have one room available in the paradise tower Room 729 (newly renovated) that i could give you, i said fine and we left happy. the room in the paradise tower was remodeled in 2003? Everything in there looks from the early 80's. Upon check out we waited in this huge line, we got to the desk and the lady got our room number, she was rude no thank you, attitude, i asked her where i could get a bellman to help with our luggage, she said in a rude tone &quot; sir its sunday, its gonna be a long while until they help you&quot; and rolled her eyes. I never be treated so bad as a guest of a hotel. this hotel needs to be torn down and be replaced with a newer casino/resort. We probarly would of got better service at motel 6 down the street.	
