Sep 27 2008 	Harder and harder to love	We just got back from our third stay at the Tropicana. We've always loved it; while it's never been the nicest place in town, we love the tacky, 1970s porno luau theme of the Island tower.Kitschy and so Vegas. We love that you can take the elevator right down to the pool, or right to the parking lot. We love the sprawling tropical pool, the location, and the price.But it's sad that every time we go, it's a little more run down. This time, just about everything was broken, burned out, worn out and battered. The place has so much potential, can't they put just a little money into it? Maybe some new carpet and a good cleaning?Don't get me wrong, if you can overlook the shortcomings, it's still a good value. For about $50 a night, we got a huge room in a great spot with a view of the strip and a really nice pool. The staff was nice. For now, we'll continue to ignore the worn out carpeting and dead lightbulbs. But if they continue to run it down, our next stay may be our last.	
