Aug 17 2008 	Great rate...location....good experience!	After reading some of the reviews posted (having just returned from 4 nights at the Tropicana), I wonder why some of the negative reviewers would choose an older hotel when there is lots of spit, polish and glitz to choose from in Las Vegas......IF YOU WANT TO PAY FOR IT. I wasn't expecting the Bellagio so I was quite content with the Island Tower room which we requested. Our check-in was quick albeit the walk from the lobby to our rooms was a bit long (suggest wheeled luggage....there are no bellhops)......yes, there is a surcharge for the use of the pool, gym and health club (it was not included in our expedia rate)....the facilities (pool and spa) were clean and well maintained. The gardens....well cared for. Our room overlooked the garden and pool.......no terraces.....good a/c......6 elevators serving the tower......our room was cleaned thoroughly each day....older facilities (ie. decor) should not be confused with cleanliness......the buffet was ok (I wasn't expecting 5 star) but hey this is Las Vegas........walk 5 minutes to the next hotel and eat there........(Excalibar has a great buffet........but the hotel itself was a little tooooooo theme oriented for me).........so to be helpful to those contemplating the Tropicana.......go if you like low key, clean, convenient.......don't go if you want the GLITZ........the MGM Grand is next door (just be ready to spend lots more $$$$).	
