Aug 8 2008 	Great view of the strip	We stayed here on our way to some National Parks. We usually stay at ExCaliber when in Vegas, but the Tropicana offered cheaper rates and was just across the street. The room itself was great; a little outdated, but very clean, with little touches of faded luxury. The bed was very comfortable, the sheets a good quality, and from the 16th floor Island Tower we had a fabulous view of both the Tropicana's lush gardens and the Strip. (I hear it will be remodeled this yearIt was very inconvenient...no clear instructions of where to park (they had covered parking plus a guest parking lot)....it took awhile to find where to check in, but that went smoothly.....to get to our room we had to cross the casino, go up a small escalator, down a long hall (convention center and shopping mall), make a turn, then found elevators. But once we found our room and learned our way around, we enjoyed it. We ate at the buffet in the casino; it was OK but nothing to write home about. Other casinos have much better food.The hotel is on the strip, but the strip is extremely busy. To cross the street, you go to one of the tramway overpasses, which should be accessible by escalator at decent distances apart. However, NONE of the escalators were working, so we had to climb stairs (about 50 per flight).....the streets were filthy, littered with nude pictures and non-english speaking people were waving placards advertising prostitutes and dirty shows. If we go again, it will be on the other end of the strip where Ceasars Palace, etc. are located.The staff was professional and helpful.	
