Aug 3 2008 	I Love the Trop!	I knew what to expect at the Trop., a great price, a great pool, and a great location. I also expected old rooms, bad food, and non existent drink service on the casino floor. The positives FAR outweighed the negatives. I paid $37 a night and got a $50 discount from Orbitz. My total with tax was $206 for 4 nights (plus service charge). I tipped the desk clerk $20 and was upgraded from the cheapest room (Garden room) to a MUCH nicer room in the Paradise tower. Table games were good, slots and video poker were horrible. I spent every day at the adult pool, which was a blast! A wide variety of fun people.The Celebration Bar had a great band every night 9 - 2am. Had an awesome time talking to people from all over the world! I vacation a lot throughout the U.S. I'm used to staying at Hampton Inns, Best Westerns and the like. The tropicana was in the same category for quality of the rooms, and was much better in terms of the pool and fun atmosphere.I would highly reccommend the Tropicana for older singles, couples, and families looking for a fun Vegas hotel without the outrageous prices and pretentiousness found at the Mega Resorts.	
