Jul 23 2008 	Typical Tropicana aged but still great...	We have been staying at Tropicana for almost 16 years. We have stayed at a few other resorts, b ut prefer the classic feel of the Trop and like the fact that the pool is less than 5 minutes from our room. I have been reading some of the poor reviews recently and also know something about Tropicana’s business situation and went into this with a reviewers eye and attitude.I arrived for a slot tournament on Thursday, July 17th. Check in was smooth, quick and my room in the Island Tower was ready on arrival. When I went to the room is was typical Tropicana: Dated, but clean. Drab bed spread and drapes. My view of the pool and strip were exceptional. I headed for the pool where there was a party atmosphere. People complain that the pool isn’t clean. I can tell you that for some part this is true, but it is primarily due to the extensive and mature landscaping in the area. When you have exotic tropical plants and trees and wind, you will have lots of debris. Most of what I found in the pool was landscape related (other than a few plastic cups). The drink service was good at the pool and there was ample booze in each drink. They were doing Caribbean Jerk sandwiches and other BBQ stuff at the pool and I found the meals served there were above average for the price. Breakfasts at the buffet were pretty decent-about average of what you find on the strip. Dinners at the Garden Café were average as well. The meals provided at the slot tournament were above average and a hosted bar was nice as well. The bars were above average with friendly bartenders for the most part, and quick service. I was rarely in need of a fresh drink. I played video poker at the bars, and some rapid roulette, where the attendants were fun, but drink service pretty slow. Housekeeping was ample and my room was kept clean and stocked for the entire 5 nights. They had a Mint Mondays pool party on Monday night, which was a little crowded and crazy for me, but the band was outstanding. The band at the celebration lounge (Friends) was great, as always and lots of people, including my wife and I, danced it up. The band covers almost anything and it very versatile. I locked my keys in my room one night and security showed up within minutes to let me into my room. I also had a problem computing my comp points, but it was taken care of quickly by front desk staff most of which were very courteous (except for a few old grouches). Overall the Tropicana was a great value and stood out again as a aged gem that isn’t for everyone. Those who don’t mind the old school Vegas style will love it. Those who are more inclined for the ultra new, squeaky clean mega resort, avoid it because you will probably find something to complain about.	
Jul 22 2008 	Old hotel but great service staff	My sister and I stayed at the Tropicana in July 2008 because of the location and great pool! We had five kids with us ranging in age from seven to seventeen. Check in was swift and the front desk was very helpful. We stayed in the standard garden room which definitely needs an over haul but it was a place to sleep. Our room was on the ground floor so parking was great because we could just hop over the balcony to the vehicle. The pool was only open until 7 pm at night which we weren't happy about. We like to be out all day and relaxing at night by the pool but on Mondays they have a pool party and then the pool is open until 11 pm. We had a great time at the pool party!!!! We are not big gamblers at all but by signing up for their players card and putting about $ 50.00 each in the slots we recieved 4 free tickets to Dirk Arthurs Extreme Magic Show -which the kids Loved!!!- and 4 free tickets to Foles Berege Show-which was wonderful!!-. While we were at the magic show we met a very nice couple who also gave us their four comped tickets to Foles so we could bring the kids. We found all the people that worked there to be very willing to help us out with what we needed. We were never in need of a drink in the casino-the waitresses were great! We found the atmosphere of the Tropicana to be very upbeat and a lot of fun even though the rooms sure need updating!!!	
