Jun 9 2008 	Pool Still Great but ...	Stayed Thurs, Fri, Sat Nights. I am a LV local and stay with my buddies when they came in to town. I am fully aware of the Trops change of ownership and almost closing and how the place has been neglected. We stayed in the Garden rooms and changed once as a bed was bad (saggy). The rooms are old and like a cheap motel. The second room had a rusty bathtub drain. The rooms were clean and the maid staff does a great job under advese conditions. The hallways in the Garden rooms are old and dingy. The second room was on the third floor and we had a nice little patio facing the small adults only pool. The AC worked perfect and would turn the room into an igloo. Pool: The pool was great. They have lots of shade from big trees and on Sat had a live band. Pool volleyball is a added bonus. Food: Garden Cafe was good for lunch and breakfast but for some reason no pancakes or French toast. They are probably are too cheap to cheap to buy a new griddle.Had the worst pastrami of my life at Players Deli next to the Leroys sports book. They need to emply the trashs cans around the property more frequently. Sun morning almost all cans were overflowing and I did not see anybody till around noon addresssing this. Makes the property feel messy and unkept.Staff: Everyone I spoke to was very friendly and helpful. Location: Thats the main reason to stay here. Walk to Excalber, NYNY, MGM etc. Met several groups going to see Kenny Chesney at MGM. Price: You get what you pay for.If you are on budget and want good pool action, and can tolerate the room conditions, then the Trop may be ok for you, but just stay away from the Players Deli.	
Jun 7 2008 	Faded but fine	It's faded, but it's fine, especially at $49 a night -- the current base rate, if you don't count the phony $7.95 a night &quot;resort fee.&quot; We stayed three nights on a package deal, were booked for a garden room, but upgraded to Island Tower without asking and/or charge. The room was large, clean and comfortable. Who could ask for more? Nothing broken, moldy, etc., as some reviews have mentioned. Sure, the hall carpet has wrinkles, and the decor is hopelessly out of date, but who cares? Even the ceiling/walls mirrors are a kick. Only complaint was dirty windows -- haven't been washed in a while. Room was cleaned and made up promptly every day. All the staff we encountered were friendly -- well, a couple dealers were unfriendly, but that's a Strip tendency. The swimming pool/garden area is beautiful -- a throwback to the Trop's glory days, and well maintained. We only ate at the breakfast buffet and in the deli, and both were good.The Strip location is great, and it's nice to find $5 blackjack and craps tables at a Strip resort. If you're on a budget and want to stay on the Strip, this is the place. But for a really great inexpensive experience, try the Main Street Station downtown.	
