Apr 6 2008 	All in all happy with my stay	Sure, this resort isn't as nice as many on the strip. Especially the casino, which is quite &quot;dowdy&quot;. But I was in Vegas for six nights for a certification class, and was on a budget but wanted to stay on the strip. The price was right at the Tropicana. Overall I was pleasantly surprised and happy with my stay. My room was large, and I had a balcony overlooking the pool area, which I loved. The room was &quot;tired&quot; with the old furniture, flowered print bedspreads and original prints on the walls - but almost had an old Vegas &quot;kitsch&quot; factor to it all! But the bed was comfy, sheets were decent, and my room was clean. Staff and guests were very friendly and down-to-earth. The pool is nice. The place is huge and there's just about anything you could want either at the Tropicana or across the street at MGM Grand. Keep in mind that everything is expensive - cigarettes in the gift shop were twice as much as they were off the strip, for example - but I found this to be true everywhere on the strip and not just at the Tropicana. I wasn't happy with being dinged with a &quot;resort fee&quot; of over $7 per night after I'd already paid in full, but wasn't going to argue at check-in about that after a long flight. All in all if you're not to snobby about your hotels I would say this is a safe choice. A cab driver told me they're soon going to impolode the whole place except for one tower and that it will be nice and huge in a couple of years.	
