Mar 24 2008	Implode it Now!!!	This hotel, resort, casino is definitely near its end. Every day its open is just a cash grab before its inevitable destruction.If the price to stay here reflected how much of a dump this place has become it might actually be tolerable. I guess they bank on their past reputation and convenient 4 corners location to continue to charge much more than they should. They are still listed on many sites as 3 star, they have not been worthy of more than 2 stars for years.We had a fantastic stay here about 12 years ago and even then you could see that it was near its end.We have stayed at better hotels like Luxor and MGM, as well as similarly rated hotels like Excalibur and Sahara. I would stay at any of these other before returning to Tropicana.Our last stay there was abysmal. So much went wrong and absolutely nothing went right. Instead of letting it ruin my vacation I decided to just laugh at our ridiculous rooms and how the staff couldn’t care less and make that part of the whole experience.I think even the staff know that they work in a dive. They are all probably wishing they worked at a better resort. It sure seems that way.The main reasons to stay at the Tropicana are the convenient location and the pool. The pool area is still pretty good and the location is the location. If that is important to you at any cost, this is the place for you. Otherwise, there are so many other choices at the same price or a little more that have so much more to offer.	
