Mar 16 2008	$7 daily "resort fee"	Be aware of the $7 per day per room &quot;resort fee&quot;. This is charged even though it gives you basically nothing during the non-summer season. The hotel even has service charges for shows at their own hotel. I stayed in the Paradise Tower and the room was acceptable.The location is really good.For the buffet spend the extra $5-$10 at a better hotel. It's well worth it. Don't bother with the buffet at Paris, there's always a lineup.Other hotels have free airport shuttles, the Tropicana doesn't. Cab from/to the airport is $10. Don't tell the cab driver it's your first time in Vegas otherwise you will get the $20 ride. -)Grand Canyon-South Rim bus tour you can find for $100, just shop around(advertised for $150).Hoover Dam bus tour is around $50.If you're from Canada and into sports check out a UNLV college game.Bring comfortable shoes as you might be walking a lot.The Deuce bus for $5 for 24 hours is a bargain with good service.	
