Feb 11 2008 	Not the best but not bad either	Stayed at the Tropicana Hotel and Casino this past weekend, and I have to say some of the reviews have been bad, but I think I know why. If you book the cheapest room, like I did, you will get a basic room that looks no better than what you would get at a chain motel like a super 8 with a bad view. I did not want that to be my room for my trip to Vegas, so I went to the front desk and asked for an upgrade. They charged me $10 more per night and put me in the Paradise tower. I was on the 16th floor, with a view of the airport, but you know what? the room was not bad. the bed was not the most comfortable, but I hardly slept anyway (Vegas style). There was a mirror ro the side and top of the bed which made me decide that I need to lose weight, so I walked all over the strip instead of taking a taxi or a bus. The light was not too bright, and the TV is small, but again I hardly spent time in the room. The Black jack tables were mostly good to me, but what ever I made at the black jack tables, the slots and wild poker took right back. The buffett is NOT worth the money, so look for somewhere else to eat. The excalibur and Luxor buffetts are way better, and are close by, or go to Caesar's Palace for some really good food, maybe a bit expensive, but I think worth the price. Most of the dealers at the tables were great, Lee and &quot;Nish&quot; were super cool. And most of them help you understand the games if you ask. Management was mostly helpful, and they have Karaoke night most nights, I did that and it was a blast. Also, you may want to check Dirk Arthur, he puts on a good show. I got comp tickets to see it, and got his autograph at the end of the show.Overall the Tropicana is a bit old, not as fancy as the other places, but I had fun. Remember, the room upgrade is worth it, and management and employees were helpful	
