Dec 17 2007	Great time at the Trop	I stayed at the Trop. for 6 nites in early November of this year and really enjoyed my stay.. Had a good rate for a Garden room which I wanted to stay in because I heard they will be coming down soon and wanted to experience some &quot;old Vegas&quot;. The room was clean, spacious, mostly quiet, and had a patio, I was on the first floor with a short walk to the casino and liked that I never had to wait for an elevator....Yes this place is older and could use some updates, which I wish they would do as I will be sorry to see it go.There are not many places like this left on the Vegas strip, which is a shame because the mega resorts are for the most part over rated, too big, and not worth the extra expense.All the employees were friendly and helpful, food at the coffee shop was good, room service was prompt and their pizza was wonderful...............The slots were VERY TIGHT.....but not just here........I visited many of the other casinos and NEVER saw anyone winning anything which never used to be the case...the only machines that gave me any play at the trop were the small bank of video poker machines that still accepted quarters....what is up with that?I would have no problem staying there again.......if it is still there..	
