Dec 2 2007 	One Fine Hotel	As some others mentioned, I too, was a little skeptical after reading the reviews on this site. However, I found the Tropicana to be a fine place to stay. Great location. Great history. Great service.My husband and I stayed Nov 28-Dec 1. We were to be in the Garden rooms, but in friendly conversation with Franne at check-in, she found out we were celebrating our anniversary and my husband's birthday. She immediately worked on getting us an upgraded room to a jacuzzi suite, free of charge, and she hooked us up with reservations for a birthday dinner at Lawry's Prime Rib.. that came with free dessert. The room was just fine, a little dated, but clean and spacious. And the dinner was excellent! We found the casino to be very friendly and with the only $5 Blackjack tables on the strip.  It's not a secret the hotel is old. It's due for some renovations, which I heard that the Garden rooms will be coming down soon and the towers to be remodeled. Our first trip to Vegas and we were very pleased. We had a great time and would stay here again.	
