Nov 29 2007 	Still Kickin'	We stayed at the &quot;Trop&quot; over Thanksgiving weekend and had a wonderful time. The Easter Island statues that once loomed over the Tropicana's facade are long gone, replaced by a neon waterfall that tumbles down the side of the hotel. Despite this place being a leftover from the old Vegas of yesteryear, we found it to be kept up adequately with all the needed amenities. We stayed on the 15th floor of the Island Tower--this was VERY comfortable--quiet w/an extraordinarily comfortable king-size mattress--I must add that the mirrored ceiling above the bed added extra pizzaz (I thought all that went out in the 1970's and was pleasantly surprised!). The bathtub was huge--the perfect size for an intimate bath for two. Also, LOCATION, LOCATION, LOCATION--how can you argue with being right across the street from five brand newer casinos--Mandalay Bay, Luxor, Excaliber, MGM Grand, and New York New York. My only complaint would be the very mediocre food situation. In all fairness we only dined at the Garden Restaurant and Island Buffet preferring to go outside the hotel for more expensive meals. The Garden Restaurant food was horrible--our waiter was disinterested and snotty (though his assistants were very sweet and attentive). The Island Buffet was grossly overpriced, crowded and noisy. The gardens in the pool area of the hotel are still lush but one of the mail ponds had been drained which subtracted from what used to be a perfect rendition of an island paradise. Overall, however, I would stay there again.	
Nov 28 2007 	Great Value	My wife and I visit Las Vegas about once a year and have stayed at the Tropicana everytime. The reason we come back is because of the great value for the location. On this visit, we were a little worried due to all the negative blogs I've read through Trip Advisor and other sites. Let me set the record straight...THIS IS STILL THE GREAT VALUE WE HAVE ALWAYS ENJOYED IF NOT BETTER!!! The room we reserved was in the Island Tower. We were on the 12th floor with a great view of the courtyard and the strip. The room was clean, the carpet (although not perfect) was not nearly as bad as everyone says...and we peeked into a few rooms to see what all the hype was about and found no evidence of neglect. We did find...friendly employees, clean areas, everything working. WHAT ARE SOME OF YOU TALKING ABOUT??? Don't come to the Tropicana if you're looking for a new hotel, but if you're looking for a great value, in a great location, with clean accommodations, and a friendly staff...this is the place!!!	
Nov 28 2007 	Great Old School Vegas Hotel	Our hotel room was very nice with a sitting area and fantastic view of the strip. The cleaning department did an excellent job daily. Overall, the staff is outstanding from check in to maintenance workers. Everyone on staff always smiled and greeted us throughout the hotel. Some of the blackjack dealers are all business, but this was a rarity. The buffet is very good but is overpriced as is the cafe. The deli has very good food at affordable prices and the service there is quick and efficient.The hotel was built in the 50s and still has that old Vegas charm, but has been updated so the rooms and overall resort are up to par. This is not a 5 star hotel, but is an excellent value for the money. Become a member of the slot club so you can get half priced tickets to the shows there. The daytime magic show and Folies are both very good. Also, the Comedy Club is very good. We saw Jimmie Walker there and he was outstanding.	
