Oct 24 2007	Your expectations should be realistic......	Our expectations were realistic, based on what we paid for this property and we had an enjoyable stay. This was our first stay at the Tropicana.We booked on line directlyh with the hotel and as they indicated they would, they had absolutely no problem with matching a lower rate I found on another website. They were very quick to respond to the request off their website and we were very, very pleased by their customer service on this request.We booked a Tower room and were immediately upgraded when we got there - didn't even ask. Very nice. Got through check in with no problem and no wait. Rooms: As most have said, this is an older property and it does have signs of it's age. The rooms are nothing special, although I LOVED that there was a window we could actually open. Basically the rooms are Holiday Inn style with a little fridge, table two chairs and a safe. We had no problems with the safe and it was free if you swiped your drivers license. Never saw the maid, room was always made up. However, we were almost never in the room so would not have expected to run into anyone. Casino: Mid sized, lots of everything you would expect in a casino and I thought the servers were great. Each day at the tables while there the same server actually remembered what I drank and just brought me one (actually she brought two) whenever she came around. Tipped her nicely as was treated very nicely. Did not spend much time in this particular casino.Food: We only ate at the dinner buffet here one night and it was quite honestly the absolute worst buffet I have ever been to in Vegas. Very small, limited selections, cheap food. $17.99 a person and honestly was about $17 per person over priced. And we were hammered and we still hated it - what does that tell you! Pool: Nice, clean and larger than I expected. MUST HAVE the Volcanic Eruptions from the pool bar. I think they were $14 a piece? Or two for $14 - don't recall exactly. And trust me....after 2 of them....you will recall very little. Fantastic and every penny worth the price. Ask for a little extra 151 float on top and you will get it.The Body Exhibit: Loved it, very much worth the admission price. We were looking for an inexpensive, clean, no frills hotel on the strip and we got exactly what we were looking for. If you are expecting the Bellagio for $49 per night - you WILL be dissapointed. Amazes me that people have Bellagio, Wynn, Ceasars, Mandalay Bay expectations from this place. I've stayed at all above but Ceasars and it never occured to me to put the Tropicana in the same category as them.For those of you interested......my opinion based on value for cost and overall impression of the Tropicana:Tropicana is better than: Circus, Circus &amp; The RivieraOn equal ground with: Imperial PalaceNot anywhere near: Bellagio, Wynn, Mandalay Bay, or ParisEnjoy and have a few Long Islands at the Bellagio Sports Bar or Pain Killers at Rumjungle. You'll be sure to have a good time in Vegas.	
