Oct 17 2007	A budget traveller's destination	OK - so it's one of the older hotels on the strip. Know this going in and you won't be disappointed. What's wonderful about the Trop is 1. Its location. You're right on the Strip. Across the street (by a convenient bridge) is the MGM, and other hotels are nearby.2. Fabulous customer service. We had a wierd noise in the room, and we were really nice about it. They upgraded us to an enormous suite for the rest of our stay. 3. Everyone went out ot their way to be pleasant and accommodating. 4. The Folies Bergere is a fun show and you can get great online prices, or even a free ticket if you sign up for their players club promotionThis is usually a hotel where my 20 something daughter and her friends stay because of the price, but if I have to take a group and rent a few rooms, the price can't be beat. Good travellers roll with the punches and don't lose their cool. Maybe that's why the Trop staff was so kind to us, but I noticed that everyone, from the reservations desk to the concierge, to the ticket booth to the people in the restaurants could have given lessons in customer service to the Bellagio. I got my money's worth and then some,	
Oct 16 2007 	Great stay	We were booked at the Tropicana through a time share promotion. They paid for a Island Tower room which we upgraded for $20 per night to a Paradise Tower room. There is little walking as the elevator to the Paradise Tower is in the front of the casino. The room was very clean and very large and seemed to have been decorated with new carpeting, drapes &amp; bedding. The housekeeping staff was excellent. Every morning we had the big breakfast in the Garden Cafe which was well worth it. There is a very pretty pool area. Upon checking in with heavy luggage use the handicap ramp as there are steps at the entrance and also to the end of the check in there is another handicap ramp instead of lugging you luggage up steps. Although this is one of the older casinos it is well worth being so close to the strip with less walking through casinos to get to your room. I would stay there again. After reading some reviews I was a little wary of staying here but did not have a bad thing to say about it.	
Oct 12 2007 	Great Room for the Price! Better than I expected.	This was our first time coming to Vegas and it was a last minute trip. So we were a little hesitant about staying here after reading all of the reviews. We were pleasantly surprised. Check in is normally at 3pm ,but because we arrived early we were able to get our rooms around 11:30a/12 noonish. We stayed in the Paradise Tower room and it was clean and comfortable. There wasn't any mold or broken toilets or celings, etc that some of the reviews talked about. We loved it and would stay here again. Plus, how much time do you really stay in your room in Vegas? Not much... Bottom line good room and location for the price. The champagne brunch at the Island Buffett was pretty good too.	
Oct 11 2007 	Better than expected	I wanted a large suite for entertaining friends for my husband's 40th birthday and the price for this was fantastic. I had some trepidations after reading some negative reviews, but decided to go with my seasoned traveler instincts and booked anyway. I was quite pleasantly surprised, from the moment I stepped foot onto the nice-looking property and was greeted very warmly by bell staff, to my departure one week later. I had a suite in the paradise tower (in front of property) that was huge. A very large parlor area with separate wet bar and dining area comprised one half of the suite; a large bedroom and bath made up the other. The view was absolutely fabulous; I defy you to find a better view in Las Vegas at almost any price. With a corner location that had windows on both sides, we could see all the way down the strip to the mountains from one side and down Tropicana Avenue past Excalibur all the way to the mountains on the other. Adjacent close-up views were of New York New York, Excalibur, and MGM Grand. It looked like Disneyland. Every member of hotel staff I encountered was exemplary in their friendliness and service. Room service was very prompt; even when told it would be 45 minutes, it was less than 20. It is an older property but the pool was still nice. I do wish they had a coffee maker and microwave in the room; $10.00 plus $4.00 for delivery, plus tip is a bit steep just for a pot of coffee in the morning. The only other option is to traipse through the casino to an OK coffee bar on the ground floor. We did experience a strange smell, which was noted by other patrons in reviews, but quickly realized that it is the usual smell of many places including outdoor areas in Las Vegas. We think it might be the water that smells that way. But all in all, I couldn't be happier with this, especially considering the very reasonable price.	
