Sep 26 2007 	Incredible Value-- Right on the Strip!	We booked a room at the Tropicana when we decided to extend our stay in Vegas but did not want to remain at our current hotel. The experience was really great.The Tropicana is one of the older hotels on the strip, but if you go into things knowing that you will not be disappointed. We were able to get a room there (on a Sunday night) for $71 ($84-something after taxes and fees, etc.)-- the same price we paid for a terrible room elsewhere! Front desk staff was great, very polite and prompt. When we got to the room, we were very pleasantly surprised. It was huge compared to the cave we had had before at the same price! The two beds were comfortable, and the sheets were amazingly soft. Although the decor looked a little dated, everything was clean and welcoming. The bathroom was huge and clean, with one downspot. In the shower, I felt quite claustrophic because of the low ceilings. Additionally, there was some mold on the ceiling. That was gross, but was the only downside to this location, and I'm not sure how widespread this was throughout the hotel. For me, it was by no means a dealbreaker, especially given the bargain we got!We had a great view of the strip from our hotel window, and were overall very pleased.The casino downstairs was, again, looking a little dated, and wasn't a &quot;trendy&quot; spot, but was fun to go down and play some cards, hit the slots a little, and have some beers while we watched the football game. All in all, I was incredibly pleased with our decision to stay at the Tropicana. While it was an older hotel, it was very clean and comfortable and I would recommend this highly to any Vegas travellers.	
