Sep 16 2007 	Tropicana is cool!	Arrived at the Tropicana on Friday, 6pm, high season summer...there was a little wait at the Front Desk, and the check in was smooth! Fran was very nice, offered an upgrade for $10 more, which was worth it, because those rooms by the pool looked a little too dated (and possibly noisy)Our room was all the way at the tall back tower, a bit of a hike but quiet and not crowded at all...Fran also offered us a 1pm late check out at no charge...We were given a map of the hotel and directions to get to our room. The room was huge and comfortable, on the 17th floor overlooking the pool and the overlooking the other mega hotels on the strip-Planet Hollywood, NY NY, MGM Grand, Excalibur, Luxor, Mandalay bay...the whole city of Vegas and beyond was in view from our room! The room was pretty basic, my boyfriend and I like to get double beds rather than just a king size, the room is bigger for the same price, nice when you have friends that come over to relax and chill.There was a table and chairs as well in our room.Bathroom shower head was a bit low, and I am 5'5!Bathtub was huge! The heavy duty curtains did come in handy when going to bed, cause the lights of the strip was just too too much! Enjoyed the buffet overlooking the pool, but it is a bit too much to pay for the type of selection offered....Lots of slots and restaurants and souvenir shops to choose from. Easy walk to MGM Grand, New York, New York, Excalibur,Luxor...Be prepared to WALK, WALK, WALK...ate like a pig during my stay.Close to cheap eats-McDonalds, La Salsa, Pizza, restaurants at the other hotels etc...Huge line for the Bodies and Titanic Exhibit-be prepared to wait or try to book the tickets in advance.Didn't dare try to swim at the pool, from the 17th floor the pool water looked murky, too many people, kids...who knows what's in that water...stay at a hotel or resort away away from the strip if you want to enjoy lounging, some elbow room or to do some actual swimming...Ate at the cafe on the first floor, decent burgers and sandwiches. It takes a while to get oriented with the Tropicana, with the huge layout of the hotel. Won a bit of $$ on slots but not much....many to choose from as well. Take advantage of the coupons that they give you upon check in-found so many laying around, it's worth it to use the buy 1 get one free drink at the many bars, though I felt the bartenders grudgingly accepted the coupons...who cares, they get paid either way! The $1.50 hot dog and drink coupon is a good pick me up too in between meals! Easygoing crowd, staff and atmosphere...I love the older style hotels in Vegas! Keep the memories alive!Easy access to and from Las Vegas airport, literally right behind the Tropicana hotel...will definitely be back here again, sign up for deals online and you'll always get your money's worth!	
