rpriced for this type of hotel. Not sure how the hotel won the bid to exhibit &quot;The Bodies&quot; and &quot;The Titanic&quot; exhibitions. Would have been better suited at The Luxor or any other hotel in its rank. Don't do the Lucky $20 slots. No one wins! But everyone gets a free cheap gift from the display case. You have to pay a daily resort fee of approx $6.00 per person for access to the gym, the pool. What a rip off! The private pool is nice. All casinos in LV allow smoking but this was awful. I caught a cold a few days later probably because of the poor ventilation. We only stayed at this hotel because we found a deal through Travelocity. Never again! The hotel is so to speak a &quot;dump&quot;. Surprise it hasn't been torn down. The service is rubbish. You get what you pay for. If you have the extra $, stay somewhere else on the strip. DO NOT PAY FOR AIRPORT SHUTTLE SERVICE!!!! It is priced same as a taxi. It's a milk run to all the hotels and is unrealiable. We paid for the &quot;Grayline Airport Shuttle&quot; tickets online thru Travelocity. However, on our return journey to the McCarran Airport, we had arranged for the shuttle to collect us. It didn't turn up. We, along with another guest, waited 40 minutes outside in 100F heat. I called Grayline and was put on hold until the next available operator....I never got to talk to anyone. We were forced to take a taxi to the airport which cost, in our case, less than the shuttle. So take a taxi instead. We now know better! Oh and watchout for sales people disguised as Las Vegas Tourist Information. They can be quite aggressive. Their only purpose is to give you a sales pitch/sell you a dinner/show or some tour. They're not like your usual tourist information. It was like being in Mexico again! A bonus was the bus service known as &quot;The Deuce&quot;. Good value for any visitor without a car. We used &quot;The Deuce&quot; to get to and fro the strip. The Deuce runs 24hrs and costs $2.50 one way or $5.00 all day. There are three outlet malls which are easily accessible thru public transit. We liked the Premium Outlet Mall just passed Stratosphere hotel on Grand Central Parkway.	
