Sep 9 2007 	You get what you pay for!!	We have just returned from Vegas, having stayed 10 days at the Tropicana hotel. It was a last minute booking, just 3 days before we went, so we went for a cheap holiday and that is what we got with this hotel. This hotel is basic, dated and without the razzle dazzle of other hotels on the strip. We had a basic room, it was clean and we had our beds made every day,it was always spotless. The room had a smell to it that wasnt altogether pleasant, but how much time do you spend in your room in vegas??....not much. The beds were comfy and we had a terrace outside with chairs, although there is a footpath directly outside the rooms, so we kept our curtains closed the whole time as people could see in. I have read other reviews about this hotel, where people say the buffet is lovely....We have to disagree!! the buffet was rubbish!! if you want a good buffet for half the price, get a cab to the Gold coast off the strip, their buffet is one of the best we`ve been to and also the Orleans Hotel,$6.99.One thing i found very alarming, is that the side doors to this hotelhave no security whatsoever, no-one to stop people coming in,no-one looking at your room keys, no device to swipe your room key before entering the side doors, so ANYONE from outside has direct access to corridors/bedrooms. We never saw one security guard on any corridors the whole ten days we were there. In the early hours of one morning, we had someone trying to get into our room and although we had the deadlock on and knew they couldnt get in, it was still very scarey...knowing any member of the public can enter the hotel by outer doors and not be challenged.When you go into other hotels on the strip and off it, you dont get anywhere near the bedrooms!!The best feature of the hotel is by far the pool area, which is lovely.Basically you get what you pay for at this hotel. We wont be staying there again and wouldnt recommend it either.	
Sep 6 2007 	Unbeatable Value!	My husband and I are in our mid thirties and are from New Zealand. We stayed at the Tropicana for a week in September 2006 after I spent hours researching accommodation options on the internet. We were absolutely thrilled with it in every respect. For anyone wanting to spend a little less on accommodation but still have a clean, spacious room with great service and amenities then I totally recommend the Tropicana. It is like an oasis amongst some very expensive and newer hotels at about one tenth the cost. The location is absolutely brilliant as it is in the midst of a small cluster of hotels (MGM Grand, Excalibar, Luxor, Hooters and New York, New York) which are great to wander through and is on the corner of one of the busiest intersections in the country. There were plenty of activities and shows and sights to see within easy walking distance and there's really no need to stay in the centre of The Strip as the monorail and bus services are great. The service was excellent. We had a small complaint to make at one stage and we received most satisfactory compensation. The rooms were clean and reasonably sized for the two of us, and we had a small balcony. Room servicing was great. Everything was clean and tidy with beds made and clean towels every day when we returned to our room. The restaurants in the hotel were excellent. The international food alley at Times Square in the New York, New York hotel across the street was great also and very handy to walk across to. The Mexican food was fantastic (I can't remember the name of the restaurant). Great roller coaster ride around the outside of the building too! Once you've ridden it you can ride again on the same day half price. Also, the magic show and the Folies Bergere show at the Tropicana were both outstanding. I'd highly recommend seeing both. The pool area was just lovely. Very large pool that was nice and clean and we spent the last day just relaxing by the water. Nice whirlpools there too if it gets a little cool. Our check-in and check-out was swift with no long queues I've heard you can get at some of the huge hotels. We had an absolutely fantastic time and we will definitely stay at the Tropicana again on our next trip to Las Vegas in 2008!	
