Jul 5 2007 	Not bad at all	My boyfriend and I stayed at the Tropicana for 2 nights this past weekend, and thought it was more than decent. After reading a lot of reviews on here (the majority of them being negative), I had a lot of doubts, but it suited us just fine. I'm sure the factor that attracts most people to the Tropicana is the price, and that's exactly why we stayed there. What do you expect for $49.95 a night? You can't compare an older hotel like this to the Bellagio, or Venetian. Some of the people that posted reviews on here about Tropicana complained about the cleanliness and decor of the room, but I found both those things exceeded the expectations I had in the room we were given. (Granted, mirrors on the ceiling aren't the classiest touch, but we couldn't stop laughing about them). The only thing that was irritating was the wait in line to check in (almost 30 mins). But the pool was nice, and the casino was fine. We didn't eat at the buffet there, so I can't really say how that was. But overall, if you're a fan of this side of the strip, and are looking for a cheap stay, then this is the place. Otherwise, don't come to Vegas if you're planning on staying in your room the whole time.	
